#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:13
msgid "Brush tip"
msgstr "ブラシ形状"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:13
msgid "Brush Mask"
msgstr "ブラシマスク"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:19
msgid "Brush Tips"
msgstr "ブラシ形状"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:23
msgid ".. image:: /images/brushes/Krita_Pixel_Brush_Settings_Popup.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:27
msgid "Auto Brush"
msgstr "自動ブラシ"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:29
msgid ""
"The generic circle or square. These brush tips are generated by Krita "
"through certain parameters."
msgstr ""
"汎用的な円や四角形です。これらのブラシ形状はパラメーターを使って Krita が生成"
"します。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:32
msgid "Types"
msgstr "タイプ"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:34
msgid ""
"First, there are three mask-types, with each the circle and square shape:"
msgstr "最初に3つのマスクタイプがあり、それぞれを円と四角形の形では:"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:38
msgid ""
"This is the ultimate generic type. The Fade parameter produces the below "
"results. Of the three auto brushes, this is the fastest."
msgstr ""
"これが最も汎用的なタイプです。減衰パラメーターは下のような結果になります。3つ"
"の自動ブラシの中では、これが最も高速です。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:40
msgid "Default"
msgstr "既定"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:43
msgid "This one's fade is controlled by a curve!"
msgstr "これの減衰はカーブによって操作します！"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:44
msgid "Soft"
msgstr "ソフト"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:47
msgid ""
"This one uses the gaussian algorithm to determine the fade. Out of the three "
"auto brushes, this is the slowest."
msgstr ""
"減衰をガウシアンアルゴリズムを使用して生成します。3つの自動ブラシの中で、これ"
"が最も遅いです。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:49
msgid "Gaussian"
msgstr "ガウシアン"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:52
msgid "Parameters"
msgstr "パラメーター"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:54
msgid "Diameter"
msgstr "直径"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:55
msgid "The pixel size of the brush."
msgstr "ピクセルでのブラシサイズです。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:57
msgid "Whether the brush is elongated or not."
msgstr "ブラシを引き延ばすかどうかです。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:59
msgid "Ratio"
msgstr "縦横比"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:62
msgid ""
"this sets the softness of the brush. You can click the chain-symbol to lock "
"and unlock these settings. Fade has a different effect per mask-type, so "
"don't be alarmed if it looks strange, perhaps you have the wrong mask-type."
msgstr ""
"ここでブラシの柔らかさを設定します。チェーンマークをクリックすることでロック"
"したりロック解除できます。減衰はマスクタイプごとに異なる効果になるため、変な"
"見た目になっても驚かないでください。おそらくマスクタイプが違うだけです。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:66
msgid "With fade locked."
msgstr "減衰ロックの時。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:70
msgid "Fade"
msgstr "減衰"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:70
msgid "With fade separately horizontal and vertical."
msgstr "減衰を水平垂直に分けた時。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:73
msgid "This changes the angle a which the brush is at."
msgstr "ブラシの角度をこれで変えます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:75
msgid "Angle"
msgstr "角度"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:78
msgid "This gives the amount of tips related to the ratio."
msgstr "縦横比に基づきブラシの選択の数を決めます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:80
msgid "Spikes"
msgstr "ブラシの角の個数"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:83
msgid ""
"This determines how much area the brush-covers over its size: It makes it "
"noisy. In the example below, the brush is set with density 0%, 50% and 100% "
"respectively."
msgstr ""
"ブラシサイズのどれだけの範囲をカバーするかを決めます: これによりノイジーにな"
"ります。下の例では、ブラシ密度はそれぞれ0%、50%、100%に設定されています。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:85
msgid "Density"
msgstr "密度"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:88
msgid ""
"This changes the randomness of the density. In the example below, the brush "
"is set with randomness 0%, 50% and 100% respectively."
msgstr ""
"これは密度のランダムさを変えます。下の例ではそれぞれ、ランダムさが0%、50%、"
"100%に設定されたブラシになっています。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:89
msgid "Randomness"
msgstr "ブラシ密度のランダムさ"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:91
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:144
msgid "Spacing"
msgstr "描点間隔"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:92
msgid ""
"This affects how far brushes are spaced apart. In the below picture, the "
"three examples on the left are with spacing 0, 1 and 5."
msgstr ""
"これはブラシがどれだけの間隔を空けるかに影響します。下の画像は、0、1、5にした"
"例です。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:94
msgid ""
"Ticking this will set the brush-spacing to a different (quadratic) "
"algorithm. The result is fine control over the spacing. In the below "
"picture, the three examples on right are with auto spacing, 0, 1 and 5 "
"respectively."
msgstr ""
"このスイッチはブラシ間隔を異なる(二次的な)アルゴリズムに設定します。間隔の操"
"作がより良くなります。下の画像では、右の3つが自動間隔にした例で、それぞれ0, "
"1, 5になっています。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:96
msgid "Auto (spacing)"
msgstr "自動 (描点間隔)"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:99
msgid ""
"This toggles the super-smooth anti-aliasing. In the below example, both "
"strokes are drawn with a default brush with fade set to 0. On the left "
"without smooth lines, and the right with. Very useful for inking brushes. "
"This option is best used in combination with Auto Spacing."
msgstr ""
"スムーズにするアンチエイリアスを切り替えます。下の例では、二つとも減衰を0にし"
"て描いています。右がアンチエイリアスで、左がそうでないものです。主線を描くの"
"に便利です。このオプションは自動描点間隔と一緒に使うのが最も望ましいです。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:101
msgid "Smooth lines"
msgstr "アンチエイリアス"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:104
msgid "Precision"
msgstr "描点精度"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:104
msgid ""
"This changes how smooth the brush is rendered. The lower, the faster the "
"brush, but the worse the rendering looks. You'd want an inking brush to have "
"a precision of 5 at all times, but a big filling brush for painting doesn't "
"require such precision, and can be easily sped up by setting precision to 1."
msgstr ""
"これはブラシがどれだけスムーズに描画されるかを変えます。低くするとブラシは高"
"速になりますが、見た目は悪くなります。主線ブラシには常に5である方が良いでしょ"
"うが、大きな塗りつぶしブラシにはそこまでの精度は必要とせず、1に設定することで"
"簡単に速度向上できます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:107
msgid ""
"This allows you to set the precision linked to the size. The first value is "
"the brush size at which precision is at last 5, and the second is the size-"
"difference at which the precision will decrease."
msgstr ""
"これは精度をサイズに関連付けることができます。ブラシサイズの初期値に精度が最"
"大の5となり、サイズの違いにより精度を下げます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:109
msgid ""
"For example: A brush with ''starting brush size'' 10 and ''delta'' 4, will "
"have..."
msgstr "例えば: ''サイズ初期値''が10で''delta''が4のブラシの場合..."

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:111
msgid "precision 5 at size 10"
msgstr "サイズ10で精度5"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:112
msgid "precision 4 at size 14"
msgstr "サイズ14で精度4"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:113
msgid "precision 3 at size 18"
msgstr "サイズ18で精度3"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:114
msgid "precision 2 at size 22"
msgstr "サイズ22で精度2"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:115
msgid "Auto (precision)"
msgstr "自動 (描画精度)"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:115
msgid "precision 1 at sizes above 26."
msgstr "サイズ26で精度1"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:120
msgid "Predefined Brushes"
msgstr "定義済みブラシ"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:123
msgid ".. image:: /images/brushes/Krita_Predefined_Brushes.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:124
msgid ""
"If you have used other applications like :program:`GIMP` "
"or :program:`Photoshop`, you will have used this kind of "
"brush. :program:`Krita` is (mostly) compatible with the brush tip "
"definitions files of these applications:"
msgstr ""
":program:`GIMP` や :program:`Photoshop` といった他のアプリケーションを使った"
"ことがあるなら、これらのブラシを使ったことがあるでしょう。:program:`Krita` は"
"それらのアプリケーション用のブラシ形状定義ファイルに(ほぼ)対応しています:"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:126
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:133
msgid "abr"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:127
msgid "Gimp autobrush tip definitions."
msgstr "GIMP 自動ブラシ形状の定義です。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:128
msgid ":ref:`file_gbr`"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:129
msgid "Gimp single bitmap brush tip. Can be black and white or colored."
msgstr "GIMP 単一ビットマップブラシ形状。白黒、またはカラーです。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:130
msgid ":ref:`file_gih`"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:131
msgid ""
"Gimp Image Hose brush tip: contains a series of brush tips that are painted "
"randomly or in order after each other. Can be black and white or "
"colored. :program:`Krita` does not yet support all the parameters yet."
msgstr ""
"GIMP イメージホースブラシ形状:ランダムまたは順番に描画される複数のブラシ形状"
"を含んでいます。白黒、またはカラーです。:program:`Krita` はまだすべてのパラ"
"メーターをサポートしていません。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:133
msgid ""
"Photoshop brush tip collections. We support many of the features of these "
"brush files, though some advanced features are not supported yet."
msgstr ""
"Photoshop のブラシプリセットです。このブラシファイルの多くの機能をサポートし"
"ていますが、高度な機能のいくつかまだサポートされていません。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:135
msgid ""
"Note that the definition of ABR brushes has been reverse engineered since "
"Adobe does not make the specification public. We strongly recommend "
"every :program:`Krita` user to share brush tips in GBR and GIH format and "
"more complex brushes as :program:`Krita` presets."
msgstr ""
"Adobe が仕様を公開していないため ABR の定義はリバースエンジニアリングによるも"
"のであることには留意してください。:program:`Krita` ユーザが公開するブラシ形状"
"はすべて GBR と GIH 形式か、より複雑なブラシでは :program:`Krita` プリセット"
"として共有することを強く推奨します。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:137
msgid ""
"All predefined brush tips are shown in one selector. There are four more "
"options that influence the initial bitmap brush tip you start painting with:"
msgstr ""
"定義済みブラシ形状のすべては一つのセレクタに表示されます。描き始める前にビッ"
"トマップブラシ形状に影響する4つのオプションがあります:"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:139
msgid "Size"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:140
msgid ""
"Scales the brush tip. 1.0 is the native size of the brush tip. This can be "
"fairly large! When painting with variable size (for instance governed by "
"pressure), this is the base for the calculations."
msgstr ""
"ブラシ形状を拡大縮小します。1.0がそのブラシ形状の元のサイズです。これをかなり"
"大きくすることができます！サイズを(筆圧に制御させるなど)可変して描く際には、"
"これを計算の元にします。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:141
msgid "Rotation"
msgstr "回転"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:142
msgid "Initial rotation of the brush tip."
msgstr "ブラシ形状の回転の初期値です。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:144
msgid "Distance between the brush tip impressions."
msgstr "ブラシ形状の間隔です。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:149
msgid "Brush Mode"
msgstr "ブラシモード"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:154
msgid "the different modes demonstrated."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:154
msgid ".. image:: /images/brushes/brush_tip_modes.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:154
msgid "Different modes shown with different brush tips."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:156
msgid "Alpha Mask"
msgstr "アルファマスク"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:157
msgid ""
"For colored brushes, don't paint the actual colors, but make a grayscale "
"brush tip that will be colored by your selected foreground/background color. "
"Lighter areas will be interpreted as more transparent."
msgstr ""
"色の付いたブラシでは実際にその色は描かず、グレースケールブラシを作って選択さ"
"れた描画/背景色の色を描きます。明るい場所はより透明であると解釈されます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:158
msgid "Color Image"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:159
msgid ""
"Use the brush tip image exactly as it is.  Especially useful for image "
"stamps."
msgstr "ブラシ形状画像を全くそのまま使用します。特にスタンプ画像に有用です。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:161
msgid ""
"Combines the features of Alpha Mask and Image Stamp modes. Transparency is "
"preserved as it is in Image Stamp mode, but colors or gray tones in the "
"brush are replaced by the foreground color.  The Lightness values of the "
"brush tip image (if thinking in HSL mode) are preserved, so dark parts of "
"the image are dark, and bright parts are bright.  This allows image stamps "
"where you can choose the color, but preserve highlights and shadows, and can "
"even create an effect of thick paint in a brush stroke by simulating the "
"highlights and shadows caused by the texture of the paint and brush stroke "
"(sometimes called an \"impasto\" effect)."
msgstr ""
"アルファマスクとイメージスタンプモードの混合です。イメージスタンプモードにあ"
"るように透過は維持されますが、ブラシの色やグレーは描画色に置き換えられます。"
"ブラシ形状画像の(HSL モードでいう)輝度の値は維持されますので、画像の暗い部分"
"は暗く、明るい部分は明るくなります。これによりハイライトや影を残したまま色を"
"選んで画像をスタンプし、また塗りやブラシストロークのテクスチャによりハイライ"
"トと影の厚塗り効果をブラシストロークで再現することもできます(\"インパスト\"効"
"果とも呼ばれます)。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:164
msgid ""
"There are three sliders here, to control the exact feel of the current brush "
"tip in Lightness or Gradient mode:"
msgstr ""
"3つのスライダーがあり、Lightness Map やグラデーションマップでのブラシ形状の感"
"触をここで操作します:"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:166
msgid "Neutral point"
msgstr "中間点"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:167
msgid ""
"This is the lightness level that will be the same as your current foreground "
"color. Higher values than this will be lighter versions of the current "
"foreground color, and lower, darker versions of the current color."
msgstr ""
"描画色と同一の明度のレベルです。高い値は描画色より明るいものになり、低ければ"
"現在の色よりも暗くなります。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:168
msgid "Brightness"
msgstr "明度"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:169
msgid "Makes the tip as a whole brighter or darker."
msgstr "ブラシ形状を単に明るくするか暗くします。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:170
msgid "Lightness Map"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:170
msgid "Contrast"
msgstr "コントラスト"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:171
msgid "Increase the contrast between dark and light areas in the tip."
msgstr "ブラシ形状にある暗い部分と明るい部分のコントラストを上げます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/brushes/brush_settings/brush_tips.rst:173
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Use the lightness values of the brush tip image as a map to a gradient.  "
#| "Black maps to the left side of the gradient, and white to the right side "
#| "of the gradient.  The gradient used is the currently selected gradient in "
#| "the main window, so you can change the gradient quickly and easily while "
#| "painting.  This mode allows image stamps with multiple colors that can be "
#| "changed (great for flowers or other colorful vegetation), and can allow "
#| "paint brushes that have multiple colors.  Image adjustment sliders for "
#| "Lightness Map mode can be used for this mode too."
msgid ""
"Use the lightness values of the brush tip image as a map to a gradient.  "
"Black maps to the left side of the gradient, and white to the right side of "
"the gradient.  The gradient used is the currently selected gradient in the "
"main window, so you can change the gradient quickly and easily while "
"painting.  This mode allows image stamps with multiple colors that can be "
"changed (great for flowers or other colorful vegetation), and can allow "
"paint brushes that have multiple colors.  Image adjustment sliders for "
"Lightness Map mode can be used for this mode too. A tutorial for this mode "
"is here: :ref:`gradient_brush_tips` ."
msgstr ""
"ブラシ形状画像の明度をグラデーション用の割り当てに使用します。黒い部分をグラ"
"デーションの左側、白を右側に割り当てます。使用するグラデーションはメインウィ"
"ンドウにある現在選択されているグラデーションなので、描いている最中に簡単に素"
"早く変えることができます。このモードは変えられる複数色のある image stamps を"
"使うことができ(花やカラフルな植物にとても良いです)、複数色を持つペイントブラ"
"シを使うことができます。Lightness Map の画像調節スライダーはこのモードでも使"
"用することができます。"

